manufacturerProductDescription.media_text: Virfour Quiet Wired Keyboard - Trendy. Efficient. Comfort. Multifunction - Good Choice for Daily Use Comfortable, Quiet, and Satisfying to type on It's a crater-switch keyboard, but its switch options are fairly quiet, and its low-profile design means you don't have to strain your wrists upwards to reach all the keys. The chiclet keys of this wired keyboard are very quiet, and most people find them comfortable to type on A Productivity Office Keyboard We put in effort with this keyboard to get many finer details just right. it has more shortcut functions for easy instant access to your music, mail, computer, favorites ect, and you can adjust the feet on the bottom of the board for two additional incline settings.

Keep your flow state uninterrupted and your focus razor-sharp throughout the workday. The tactile feedback is just enough to satisfy without disturbing the peace.Ergonomically crafted for comfort, the Virfour Wired keyboard keeps your hands happy even during those marathon typing sessions.No drivers, no fuss! It's the plug-and-play solution for the busy professional who values time and tranquility. It's not just an addition to your desk; it's an upgrade to your productivity and comfort.

The splash-proof keycaps of this wired keyboard are specially designed for easy cleaning to prevent accidental water splashes. Never worry about accidentally spilling drinks and coffee from damaging your keyboard again. The characters on keycaps are extremely hard to wear thanks to the high quality UV coating. The 8 additional multimedia shortcuts greatly simplify your work and more focus on the task at hand.The numeric keypad of this full size wired keyboard is also great for spreadsheets and finance applications.Notes: 12 easy access shortcuts cannot be compatible with Mac. Each low profile key of the usb keyboard allows for increased stability, while optimized key travel provides a comfortable and precise typing experience. The muted chiclet key allows you to not only obtain comfortable touch and mute effect, but also enjoy the fast and sensitive of wired keyboard.
Designed to improve efficiency, it's perfect for statistics, finance, writing, accounting, programming, design, and more.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 18, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Quiet and accurate.
reviews.reviewText: Bought this to use at work because I have long nails and the keyboard they gave us at work makes too much click clack noises. I type fast too so it just made a bunch of racket and draws too much attention as I work with a lot of people in the same room. This keyboard made a HUGE difference and feels nice to type on. Connecting was super easy and within minutes, I was able to start working! Very easy to clean too and I love how light it is.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on March 10, 2023
reviews.reviewText: This keyboard is exactly as advertised and is fantastic for the price point. It is quiet, sleek, and very functional. The selling point for me was the additional volume / music control buttons, and the calculator button. I could not find all of those on any other "quiet" keyboard in this price range. The only con is that it feels like the keys are a bit too close together. My fingers tend to graze the edge of other keys somewhat frequently, a "problem" I've never experienced on another keyboard. I think generally on these chiclet keyboards the keys themselves are spaced a little further apart. Regardless, it is still a 5-star product due to its layout and quietness.

reviews.reviewText: I'm an animator who needs a silent keyboard because I share a room with someone sensitive to clicking sounds. This worked perfectly; it's incredibly quiet, but easy to work with. It doesn't feel cheap either, not like the lightweight plastic keyboards. There is no lag either. 10/10.
